    "body": "## Problem\n\nThere is no way for a user to tell `:restart` to \"run this command(s) after restarting\". For example, when installing plugins, user may want to run update() after restarting:\n\n    :restart lua vim.pack.update()\n\nNote that \"just put it in your init.lua\" isn't an answer because the current Nvim may be running with `-u NONE` or `--clean`, etc.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nAll `:restart` args following the optional `+cmd` arg https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/34788 are treated as a big cmdline that is passed as a `-c` CLI arg when restarting nvim.\n\n    :restart +qall! lua vim.pack.update()\n\nThe above example:\n\n1. quits the current server using `:qall!`\n2. restarts a new server with `-c lua vim.pack.update()`",
